commit.message: more updates to cope with changes for notebook 5.x

Merge pull request #6 from haobibo/master

import ArgumentConflict from notebook.extension
split ArgementConflict import to another try/catch block

import ArgumentConflict from notebook.extension

After notebook 5.0, the `ArgumentConflict` is moved to `notebook.extensions`.
This commit will make dependencies of jupyter_contrib_core (e.g.: jupyter_nbextensions_configurator) to import the right `ToggleServerExtensionApp` and `toggle_serverextension_python`, which is provided by `notebook.serverextensions`, instead of `jupyter_contrib_core.notebook_compat._compat.serverextensions`.
[CI] can only use conda < 4.3.14 on travis
make conda recipe use git-based version & build number

CI & packaging fixes
* fix appveyor py35 env to match others
* attempt to get appveyor to pass even if codecov fails
* use `coverage combine` with `--append` flag, required since 4.2

add `_maybe_copy` and `_should_copy`
to `notebook_compat._compat.nbextensions`, as the logger kwarg was added after notebook 4.1
